3:
Yahweh my God, I never did what my enemies say I did;
\q there is no injustice on my hands.
\q

6:
Arise, Yahweh, in your anger;
\q stand up against the rage of my enemies;
\q wake up for my sake and carry out the righteous decrees that you have commanded for them.
\q

8:
Yahweh, judge the nations;
\q vindicate me, Yahweh, because I am righteous and innocent, Most High.
\q
